## 3. Report – ONLY Playwright test results (detailed per test)

- **Problem:** Report contained cross-deps, artifacts, test case file lists, etc. User wanted **only** Playwright test results.
- **Rule:** The HandsOff report saved as **`Cursor-Project/reports/YYYY-MM-DD/{JIRA_KEY}.md`** MUST be focused **only on Playwright test results**:
  - **Per test:** (1) Test name/title, (2) **What is verified** (detailed: which endpoint, which assertions, which behaviour), (3) **Steps** (brief list), (4) **Result:** Passed / Failed / Not run, (5) **If failed:** reason (assertion message, status code, response body or error snippet).
- **Rule:** Do not fill the report with cross-dependency output, test case file listings, or generic "artifacts" sections. Optional: one short line with spec file path and how to run (e.g. `npx playwright test --grep "NT-1"`).

Reference: Rule 0.6 (report generation); `.cursor/commands/hands-off.md` Step 6.

---

## 4. Slack – Send FULL report ONLY to Tester (DM) and #ai-report – NEVER to anyone else

- **Problem:** The message sent to Slack was too brief; user wanted the **full report**. Sometimes the report was sent to Assignee or other users; it must go only to Tester and #ai-report.
- **Rule (template):** The content sent to Slack MUST follow the **Slack report template** structure every time. Use **`Cursor-Project/config/Slack_report_template.md`** as the canonical format. The message MUST include: (1) Header: `{JIRA_KEY} – Playwright test results`; (2) Jira, Title, Date, Assignee / Tester; (3) Total: X passed, Y failed, Z skipped; (4) Separator `-------------------------`; (5) For each test: `Test N: [JIRA_KEY] short title – short details`, then **Test description**, **Expected result**, **Actual result**, **Test result**. Fill all placeholders from the Jira ticket and Playwright run. Same structure for every HandsOff Slack report.
- **Rule (ONLY two recipients – CRITICAL):** The report must be sent **only** to (1) the **Tester** (DM) and (2) the **#ai-report** channel. **Do NOT send the report to Assignee or to any other Slack user.** Never send to only one of the two when both are applicable; send the **full report content** to the Tester via `slack_send_message(channel_id: <tester_user_id>, message: report_content)` and to **#ai-report** via `slack_send_message(channel_id: "C0AK96S1D7X", message: report_content)`. **Always use** channel_id **`C0AK96S1D7X`** for #ai-report. If no Tester is set in Jira, send only to #ai-report (still never to Assignee). If the message length limit applies (e.g. 5000 chars), send the full Playwright-results section at minimum.
- **Tester from Jira – correct field only:** Always resolve the **Tester** from the ticket’s **"Tester"** custom field. In this project that is **`customfield_10095`** (single user picker). Use that user’s **displayName** for Slack. **Do NOT use** Assignee or **customfield_11151** (BA – Business Analyst). If `customfield_10095` is null, there is no Tester; send only to #ai-report.
- **Find Tester on Slack by name:** Call **`slack_search_users(query: <tester display name>)`** with the display name from **customfield_10095**; use the returned **User ID** as `channel_id` for the DM. Do **not** use hardcoded Slack user IDs; do **not** add @mention. Send the full report **only** to that Tester (DM) and #ai-report (C0AK96S1D7X). **Never send to Assignee or anyone else.**

Reference: `Cursor-Project/config/Slack_report_template.md`; `.cursor/commands/hands-off.md` Step 7; user-slack MCP `slack_send_message`, `slack_search_users`, `slack_search_channels`.

